article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Achor Achor had 18 points in Samford's 88-62 victory against Western Carolina on Wednesday night for its sixth straight victory. Achor added five rebounds for the Bulldogs (23-3, 12-1 Southern Conference). Jaden Campbell and Jermaine Marshall added 16 points apiece. Vonterius Woolbright led the way for the Catamounts (18-8, 7-6) with 21 points, 13 rebounds and two steals. DJ Campbell added 13 points for Western Carolina. Tre Jackson also had 10 points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
